# 2. MBR vs GPT

These describe how a disk stores partition information.

---

## MBR (Master Boot Record)

Located in the first sector of the disk.

Contains:

* Boot code
* Partition table
* Disk signature

Maximum

* 2 TB disk
* 4 primary partitions

Boot Process

```
BIOS
   ↓
Reads MBR
   ↓
Loads Boot Manager
```

---

## GPT (GUID Partition Table)

Modern partition style.

Supports

* 9.4 ZB disks
* 128 partitions
* Multiple partition table copies
* CRC protection

Boot Process

```
UEFI
   ↓
EFI System Partition
   ↓
bootmgfw.efi
```

---

## MBR vs GPT

| Feature     | MBR  | GPT       |
| ----------- | ---- | --------- |
| Max Disk    | 2 TB | 9.4 ZB    |
| Partitions  | 4    | 128       |
| Firmware    | BIOS | UEFI      |
| Recovery    | Poor | Excellent |
| Secure Boot | No   | Yes       |

